{"parentUuid":"2d21dbd7-01dd-4a2c-91f9-37010e145769","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ad547d9ab0a90bc64","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccqb1vBQmipoJ6xYMcuxg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me check the concurrency and enforcement tests to confirm expected semantics against the implementation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6612,"cache_read_input_tokens":43324,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6612,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccqb1uCdJCzg9k57pCHnj","attributionAgent":"Explore","attributionSkill":"code-review","type":"assistant","uuid":"db240a8e-c142-45be-9fed-5c12c7d4cd9a","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:07:49.886Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"db240a8e-c142-45be-9fed-5c12c7d4cd9a","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ad547d9ab0a90bc64","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccqb1vBQmipoJ6xYMcuxg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JusSpqNzPERbq9FAqSpUrb","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\integration\\test_quota_concurrency.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6612,"cache_read_input_tokens":43324,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6612,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccqb1uCdJCzg9k57pCHnj","attributionAgent":"Explore","attributionSkill":"code-review","type":"assistant","uuid":"ef2925b2-8180-4ab6-9391-3fe2b380c0f0","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:07:50.873Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"ef2925b2-8180-4ab6-9391-3fe2b380c0f0","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"bcf5258e-2708-4b49-a1f7-27fad0c3c471","agentId":"ad547d9ab0a90bc64","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JusSpqNzPERbq9FAqSpUrb","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"AC13: strict enforcement under concurrency. N concurrent distinct-\n2\tidempotency-key posts of `Q` against a cap `L` must never drive\n3\t`usage_rollup.total_quantity` above `L` — the `FOR UPDATE OF q` row lock in\n4\t`src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` serializes every writer for the same\n5\t`(customer, metric)`, so the excess requests are rejected 429 rather than the\n6\tcap being exceeded (`plan §\"The atomic read-and-decide\"`).\n7\t\"\"\"\n8\t\n9\timport asyncio\n10\tfrom decimal import Decimal\n11\t\n12\tfrom sqlalchemy import text\n13\t\n14\t\n15\tasync def test_concurrent_posts_never_exceed_limit(client, make_api_key, postgres_url):\n16\t    \"\"\"20 concurrent posts of quantity=1 (distinct idempotency_key) against a\n17\t    cap of 10 must land exactly 10 winners and 10 rejections, with the final\n18\t    rollup total never exceeding the cap.\"\"\"\n19\t    admin_key, api_key_id = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\", rate_limit_per_sec=1000)\n20\t    headers = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {admin_key}\"}\n21\t    limit_per_window = 10\n22\t    concurrent_requests = 20\n23\t\n24\t    quota_response = await client.put(\n25\t        \"/v1/quotas\",\n26\t        json={\"customer_id\": \"cust_concurrent\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\", \"limit_per_window\": limit_per_window},\n27\t        headers=headers,\n28\t    )\n29\t    assert quota_response.status_code == 201\n30\t\n31\t    async def _post(index: int):\n32\t        return await client.post(\n33\t            \"/v1/events\",\n34\t            json={\n35\t                \"customer_id\": \"cust_concurrent\",\n36\t                \"metric\": \"api_calls\",\n37\t                \"quantity\": \"1\",\n38\t                \"idempotency_key\": f\"concurrent-{index}\",\n39\t            },\n40\t            headers=headers,\n41\t        )\n42\t\n43\t    responses = await asyncio.gather(*(_post(index) for index in range(concurrent_requests)))\n44\t    statuses = [response.status_code for response in responses]\n45\t    winners = [status for status in statuses if status == 201]\n46\t    rejections = [status for status in statuses if status == 429]\n47\t\n48\t    assert len(winners) == limit_per_window, f\"expected exactly {limit_per_window} winners, got statuses: {statuses}\"\n49\t    assert len(rejections) == concurrent_requests - limit_per_window\n50\t    assert all(response.json()[\"error\"][\"code\"] == \"quota_exceeded\" for response in responses if response.status_code == 429)\n51\t\n52\t    from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import create_async_engine\n53\t\n54\t    engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n55\t    async with engine.connect() as connection:\n56\t        rollup = (\n57\t            await connection.execute(\n58\t                text(\n59\t                    \"SELECT total_quantity, event_count FROM usage_rollup \"\n60\t                    \"WHERE api_key_id = :id AND customer_id = 'cust_concurrent' AND metric = 'api_calls'\"\n61\t                ),\n62\t                {\"id\": api_key_id},\n63\t            )\n64\t        ).mappings().first()\n65\t    await engine.dispose()\n66\t\n67\t    assert Decimal(rollup[\"total_quantity\"]) <= Decimal(limit_per_window), \"usage must never exceed the cap\"\n68\t    assert Decimal(rollup[\"total_quantity\"]) == Decimal(limit_per_window), \"the lock must let exactly L worth land\"\n69\t    assert rollup[\"event_count\"] == limit_per_window\n70\t"}]},"uuid":"ef606c88-0850-430f-9c90-00d2013360ad","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:07:50.886Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ef2925b2-8180-4ab6-9391-3fe2b380c0f0","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"ef606c88-0850-430f-9c90-00d2013360ad","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ad547d9ab0a90bc64","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccqb1vBQmipoJ6xYMcuxg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BPreXQJSNKh5BHWsDxsCbc","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\integration\\test_events_quota_enforcement.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6612,"cache_read_input_tokens":43324,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6612,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccqb1uCdJCzg9k57pCHnj","attributionAgent":"Explore","attributionSkill":"code-review","type":"assistant","uuid":"faa685c2-a879-4640-996a-21f4fb2cff70","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:07:51.497Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"faa685c2-a879-4640-996a-21f4fb2cff70","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"bcf5258e-2708-4b49-a1f7-27fad0c3c471","agentId":"ad547d9ab0a90bc64","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BPreXQJSNKh5BHWsDxsCbc","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Integration tests for the `POST /v1/events` quota check against a real\n2\tPostgres + Redis (AC7, AC8, AC9, AC10, AC11, AC12, AC14, AC18-read-path, AC19-rejected).\"\"\"\n3\t\n4\timport json\n5\t\n6\tfrom sqlalchemy import text\n7\t\n8\t\n9\tdef _event_payload(**overrides) -> dict:\n10\t    payload = {\n11\t        \"customer_id\": \"cust_1\",\n12\t        \"metric\": \"api_calls\",\n13\t        \"quantity\": \"5\",\n14\t        \"idempotency_key\": \"idem-1\",\n15\t    }\n16\t    payload.update(overrides)\n17\t    return payload\n18\t\n19\t\n20\tdef _quota_payload(**overrides) -> dict:\n21\t    payload = {\"customer_id\": \"cust_1\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\", \"limit_per_window\": 10}\n22\t    payload.update(overrides)\n23\t    return payload\n24\t\n25\t\n26\tasync def _set_quota(client, admin_key: str, **overrides) -> None:\n27\t    response = await client.put(\n28\t        \"/v1/quotas\", json=_quota_payload(**overrides), headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {admin_key}\"}\n29\t    )\n30\t    assert response.status_code in (200, 201), response.text\n31\t\n32\t\n33\tasync def test_no_quota_is_unlimited(client, make_api_key):\n34\t    \"\"\"AC7: no quota row for (customer, metric) -> unchanged behavior, 201.\"\"\"\n35\t    admin_key, _ = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n36\t\n37\t    response = await client.post(\n38\t        \"/v1/events\", json=_event_payload(quantity=\"1000000\"), headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {admin_key}\"}\n39\t    )\n40\t    assert response.status_code == 201\n41\t\n42\t\n43\tasync def test_under_limit_accepted(client, make_api_key, postgres_url):\n44\t    \"\"\"AC8: R + Q <= L -> 201 accepted, rollup increments normally.\"\"\"\n45\t    admin_key, api_key_id = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n46\t    await _set_quota(client, admin_key, limit_per_window=100)\n47\t\n48\t    response = await client.post(\n49\t        \"/v1/events\", json=_event_payload(quantity=\"5\"), headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {admin_key}\"}\n50\t    )\n51\t    assert response.status_code == 201\n52\t\n53\t    from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import create_async_engine\n54\t\n55\t    engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n56\t    async with engine.connect() as connection:\n57\t        rollup = (\n58\t            await connection.execute(\n59\t                text(\"SELECT total_quantity FROM usage_rollup WHERE api_key_id = :id\"), {\"id\": api_key_id}\n60\t            )\n61\t        ).mappings().first()\n62\t    await engine.dispose()\n63\t    assert rollup is not None\n64\t    from decimal import Decimal\n65\t\n66\t    assert Decimal(rollup[\"total_quantity\"]) == Decimal(\"5\")\n67\t\n68\t\n69\tasync def test_over_limit_429_and_no_partial_write(client, make_api_key, postgres_url):\n70\t    \"\"\"AC9: R + Q > L -> 429 quota_exceeded with Retry-After; no event row, no rollup increment (rolled back).\"\"\"\n71\t    admin_key, api_key_id = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n72\t    await _set_quota(client, admin_key, limit_per_window=10)\n73\t\n74\t    accepted = await client.post(\n75\t        \"/v1/events\",\n76\t        json=_event_payload(quantity=\"8\", idempotency_key=\"accepted-1\"),\n77\t        headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {admin_key}\"},\n78\t    )\n79\t    assert accepted.status_code == 201\n80\t\n81\t    rejected = await client.post(\n82\t        \"/v1/events\",\n83\t        json=_event_payload(quantity=\"5\", idempotency_key=\"rejected-1\"),\n84\t        headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {admin_key}\"},\n85\t    )\n86\t    assert rejected.status_code == 429\n87\t    assert rejected.json()[\"error\"][\"code\"] == \"quota_exceeded\"\n88\t    assert \"Retry-After\" in rejected.headers\n89\t    assert int(rejected.headers[\"Retry-After\"]) >= 1\n90\t\n91\t    from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import create_async_engine\n92\t\n93\t    engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n94\t    async with engine.connect() as connection:\n95\t        rejected_event_count = (\n96\t            await connection.execute(\n97\t                text(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM events WHERE api_key_id = :id AND idempotency_key = 'rejected-1'\"),\n98\t                {\"id\": api_key_id},\n99\t            )\n100\t        ).scalar_one()\n101\t        rollup = (\n102\t            await connection.execute(\n103\t                text(\"SELECT total_quantity FROM usage_rollup WHERE api_key_id = :id\"), {\"id\": api_key_id}\n104\t            )\n105\t        ).mappings().first()\n106\t    await engine.dispose()\n107\t\n108\t    assert rejected_event_count == 0, \"a rejected event must leave no trace (transaction rolled back)\"\n109\t    from decimal import Decimal\n110\t\n111\t    assert Decimal(rollup[\"total_quantity\"]) == Decimal(\"8\"), \"the rollup must reflect only the accepted event\"\n112\t\n113\t\n114\tasync def test_empty_window_q_gt_l_rejected(client, make_api_key, postgres_url):\n115\t    \"\"\"AC10: Q > L against an empty window (no prior rollup row) -> 429; no rollup row created.\"\"\"\n116\t    admin_key, api_key_id = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n117\t    await _set_quota(client, admin_key, limit_per_window=3)\n118\t\n119\t    response = await client.post(\n120\t        \"/v1/events\", json=_event_payload(quantity=\"5\"), headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {admin_key}\"}\n121\t    )\n122\t    assert response.status_code == 429\n123\t    assert response.json()[\"error\"][\"code\"] == \"quota_exceeded\"\n124\t\n125\t    from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import create_async_engine\n126\t\n127\t    engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n128\t    async with engine.connect() as connection:\n129\t        rollup = (\n130\t            await connection.execute(\n131\t                text(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM usage_rollup WHERE api_key_id = :id\"), {\"id\": api_key_id}\n132\t            )\n133\t        ).scalar_one()\n134\t    await engine.dispose()\n135\t    assert rollup == 0, \"no rollup row should be created for a rejected first event in an empty window\"\n136\t\n137\t\n138\tasync def test_replay_over_quota_returns_200_no_usage(client, make_api_key, postgres_url):\n139\t    \"\"\"AC11: a replay of a previously accepted event, window now over quota,\n140\t    returns 200 (the original replay) — the quota is never consulted, no usage added.\"\"\"\n141\t    admin_key, api_key_id = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n142\t    await _set_quota(client, admin_key, limit_per_window=10)\n143\t\n144\t    first = await client.post(\n145\t        \"/v1/events\",\n146\t        json=_event_payload(quantity=\"8\", idempotency_key=\"replay-key\"),\n147\t        headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {admin_key}\"},\n148\t    )\n149\t    assert first.status_code == 201\n150\t\n151\t    # Lower the quota below what's already accumulated, so a *fresh* event\n152\t    # would now be rejected -- but a replay of the same idempotency_key must\n153\t    # still succeed with the original result, untouched by the new quota.\n154\t    await _set_quota(client, admin_key, limit_per_window=1)\n155\t\n156\t    replay = await client.post(\n157\t        \"/v1/events\",\n158\t        json=_event_payload(quantity=\"8\", idempotency_key=\"replay-key\"),\n159\t        headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {admin_key}\"},\n160\t    )\n161\t    assert replay.status_code == 200\n162\t    assert replay.json()[\"idempotent_replay\"] is True\n163\t\n164\t    from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import create_async_engine\n165\t\n166\t    engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n167\t    async with engine.connect() as connection:\n168\t        rollup = (\n169\t            await connection.execute(\n170\t                text(\"SELECT total_quantity, event_count FROM usage_rollup WHERE api_key_id = :id\"),\n171\t                {\"id\": api_key_id},\n172\t            )\n173\t        ).mappings().first()\n174\t    await engine.dispose()\n175\t\n176\t    from decimal import Decimal\n177\t\n178\t    assert rollup[\"event_count\"] == 1, \"a replay must never add usage\"\n179\t    assert Decimal(rollup[\"total_quantity\"]) == Decimal(\"8\")\n180\t\n181\t\n182\tasync def test_midwindow_change_takes_effect(client, make_api_key):\n183\t    \"\"\"AC12: lowering L mid-window (L <= R already accumulated) blocks the\n184\t    rest of the window immediately, against a fresh read each POST.\"\"\"\n185\t    admin_key, _ = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n186\t    await _set_quota(client, admin_key, limit_per_window=100)\n187\t\n188\t    first = await client.post(\n189\t        \"/v1/events\",\n190\t        json=_event_payload(quantity=\"20\", idempotency_key=\"midwindow-1\"),\n191\t        headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {admin_key}\"},\n192\t    )\n193\t    assert first.status_code == 201\n194\t\n195\t    # Lower the cap below the already-accumulated total (20).\n196\t    await _set_quota(client, admin_key, limit_per_window=10)\n197\t\n198\t    second = await client.post(\n199\t        \"/v1/events\",\n200\t        json=_event_payload(quantity=\"1\", idempotency_key=\"midwindow-2\"),\n201\t        headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {admin_key}\"},\n202\t    )\n203\t    assert second.status_code == 429\n204\t    assert second.json()[\"error\"][\"code\"] == \"quota_exceeded\"\n205\t\n206\t\n207\tasync def test_throttle_precedes_quota_distinct_codes(truncate_tables, make_api_key):\n208\t    \"\"\"AC14: the Tier-2 per-key throttle fires (code: rate_limited) before any\n209\t    quota logic runs; a genuine quota rejection uses the distinct quota_exceeded code.\"\"\"\n210\t    from httpx import ASGITransport, AsyncClient\n211\t\n212\t    from src.main import app\n213\t\n214\t    throttled_key, _ = await make_api_key(label=\"throttled\", rate_limit_per_sec=1, scope=\"admin\")\n215\t\n216\t    async with AsyncClient(transport=ASGITransport(app=app), base_url=\"http://test\") as test_client:\n217\t        first = await test_client.post(\n218\t            \"/v1/events\", json=_event_payload(idempotency_key=\"t-1\"), headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {throttled_key}\"}\n219\t        )\n220\t        second = await test_client.post(\n221\t            \"/v1/events\", json=_event_payload(idempotency_key=\"t-2\"), headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {throttled_key}\"}\n222\t        )\n223\t        assert first.status_code == 201\n224\t        assert second.status_code == 429\n225\t        assert second.json()[\"error\"][\"code\"] == \"rate_limited\"\n226\t\n227\t        quota_key, _ = await make_api_key(label=\"quota-key\", rate_limit_per_sec=1000, scope=\"admin\")\n228\t        await test_client.put(\n229\t            \"/v1/quotas\",\n230\t            json=_quota_payload(limit_per_window=1),\n231\t            headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {quota_key}\"},\n232\t        )\n233\t        rejected = await test_client.post(\n234\t            \"/v1/events\",\n235\t            json=_event_payload(quantity=\"5\", idempotency_key=\"q-1\"),\n236\t            headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {quota_key}\"},\n237\t        )\n238\t        assert rejected.status_code == 429\n239\t        assert rejected.json()[\"error\"][\"code\"] == \"quota_exceeded\"\n240\t\n241\t\n242\tasync def test_rejection_is_logged_without_totals(client, make_api_key, capsys):\n243\t    \"\"\"AC19: a 429 quota rejection logs `quota.rejected` (WARNING) without\n244\t    the current_total/limit numbers (structlog prints JSON to stdout).\"\"\"\n245\t    admin_key, _ = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n246\t    await _set_quota(client, admin_key, limit_per_window=1)\n247\t\n248\t    response = await client.post(\n249\t        \"/v1/events\", json=_event_payload(quantity=\"5\"), headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {admin_key}\"}\n250\t    )\n251\t    assert response.status_code == 429\n252\t\n253\t    captured = capsys.readouterr()\n254\t    rejected_lines = [line for line in captured.out.splitlines() if \"quota.rejected\" in line]\n255\t    assert len(rejected_lines) == 1\n256\t\n257\t    rejection_record = json.loads(rejected_lines[0])\n258\t    assert rejection_record[\"reason\"] == \"quota_exceeded\"\n259\t    assert \"current_total\" not in rejection_record\n260\t    assert \"limit_per_window\" not in rejection_record\n261\t    assert \"limit\" not in rejection_record\n262\t"}]},"uuid":"75827283-cc03-4b1c-9f9c-a7dee471026d","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:07:51.517Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"faa685c2-a879-4640-996a-21f4fb2cff70","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"75827283-cc03-4b1c-9f9c-a7dee471026d","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ad547d9ab0a90bc64","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccqb7TKZ56b1YMmyh2kEX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10647,"cache_read_input_tokens":49936,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":10647,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccqb7S692ujnVoh9fBpGN","attributionAgent":"Explore","attributionSkill":"code-review","type":"assistant","uuid":"5951f97b-6bae-4e6d-b801-84b4091ad128","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:09:16.458Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"5951f97b-6bae-4e6d-b801-84b4091ad128","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ad547d9ab0a90bc64","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccqb7TKZ56b1YMmyh2kEX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I performed a line-by-line scan of every hunk in the in-scope files and read the enclosing functions. Here is my assessment.\n\n## Result: No confirmed correctness bug found.\n\nThe per-customer metric-quota data path holds up under the failure-mode checks I ran. Details of what I verified (so the negative result is auditable):\n\n**Boundary semantics (`events_service.py:105`)** — `current_total + inserted.quantity > limit_per_window` correctly implements \"reject iff R+Q>L / allow iff R+Q<=L\". Checked against tests: q=8 then q=5 vs L=10 → reject (13>10); 10x q=1 winners vs L=10 → the 10th lands (9+1=10, not >10), 11th rejects. No off-by-one, not inverted.\n\n**Falsy-zero / None handling** — every branch uses explicit `is not None` (`inserted is not None`, `quota_state is not None`, `lock_row is None`, `rollup_row is not None`), so a zero `current_total`/`total=0`, or a `Decimal(0)` EventRecord, never trips a truthiness check. Missing rollup row correctly defaults to `Decimal(0)` (repo line 148); missing quota row correctly returns `None` → unlimited path.\n\n**Transaction/rollback** — `QuotaExceededError` is raised inside the `async with scoped_transaction(...)` block (line 118, indented under line 86), so `session.begin().__aexit__` rolls back the already-inserted event and skips `increment_usage_rollup`. Matches `test_over_limit_429_and_no_partial_write` (event_count 0, rollup unchanged at 8).\n\n**Concurrency / lock scope** — `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE` on the quota row serializes writers for the same `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric)`. The rollup is read in a *separate* statement after the lock, and since `scoped_transaction` uses PostgreSQL's default READ COMMITTED (session.py — no isolation override), each unblocked waiter gets a fresh per-statement snapshot that includes the prior holder's committed increment. The event INSERT happening *before* the lock is safe because enforcement keys off the rollup increment, which is under the lock. Produces exactly 10 winners / 10 rejections in the concurrency test.\n\n**Idempotent replay** — replay path (lines 137-152) never consults the quota and never increments the rollup, so lowering L below accumulated usage can't retroactively reject a replay or double-count (`test_replay_over_quota_returns_200_no_usage`, `test_midwindow_change_takes_effect`).\n\n**Retry-After window math** (`_seconds_until_next_hour_boundary`) — `received_at ∈ [window_start, window_start+1h)`, so the delta is in `(0, 3600]`, `ceil` then `max(1, …)` → always 1..3600. No timezone drift: a single `received_at`/`window_start` pair is threaded through insert, quota read, and rollup.\n\n**Migration / auth** — quotas PK `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric)` matches the upsert `ON CONFLICT`; `scope` backfills NOT NULL `'ingest'`, and `find_active_key_by_key_id` now selects it, so `AuthenticatedPrincipal.scope` is always populated (no None reaching the `!= \"admin\"` gate). RLS `USING` with omitted `WITH CHECK` defaults to the `USING` expr for INSERT, and `scoped_transaction` sets `app.current_api_key_id` matching the inserted `api_key_id`.\n\n## Sub-threshold notes (not bugs, no failure scenario)\n- The `xmax = 0` create/replace idiom (`quotas_repo.py:65`) is reliable here even under two concurrent `PUT` of the same new key — RETURNING is evaluated atomically within the upsert statement, so the loser takes the DO UPDATE path and correctly reports `inserted=false` (200). I could not construct a mis-status scenario.\n- Doc drift only: the concurrency test and repo docstring say `FOR UPDATE OF q`, but the actual query is a plain single-table `FOR UPDATE` with no `q` alias. Locks the correct row; harmless wording mismatch.\n\nIf you want, I can widen scope to the rate-limit/throttle interaction or the `EventCreateRequest`/quantity schema (validates `quantity`, negative/zero guards) — those sit just outside the files you named but feed the same comparison."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10647,"cache_read_input_tokens":49936,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":10647,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccqb7S692ujnVoh9fBpGN","attributionAgent":"Explore","attributionSkill":"code-review","type":"assistant","uuid":"1e1fb884-16ae-49ed-978e-ea7a3c084cc7","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:09:36.458Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
